{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"PermissionKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Get started with Dynamic Type","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc24-10074-get-started-with-dynamic-type","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Dynamic Type lets people choose their preferred text size across the system and all of their apps. To help you get started supporting Dynamic Type, we’ll cover the fundamentals: How it works, how to find issues with scaling text in your app, and how to take practical steps using SwiftUI and UIKit to create a great Dynamic Type experience. We’ll also show how you can best use the Large Content Viewer to make navigation controls accessible to everyone."}]}}}